text:
Following! I have two clients that use Clickup & Monday but both seem overly complex for my own needs.

At the moment I manage my own stuff in Trello with custom fields for client names and a simple pipeline process (idea dump > to-do > in progress > pending approval > done), but this doesn't always work for big or vague projects.

I started to use Airtable but couldn't really understand what I was looking at, same with Notion - I probably just need to make the time to learn them.

Interested to hear what others think! I'm with you <@U02CVNB3X1T>, they all seem to be wearing different pants... with heavy MS access vibes...
